RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 46. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.

CLAIM.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Shake and Bake Racing LLC

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLISS THIS dueled to a slim lead at the five sixteenths pole and contested even terms in the three path on the turn, drew briefly clear toward mid-stretch and dug in determinedly for the nod. FLASH OF DAY engaged in close early chase inside but steadied at the rail approaching the five sixteenths pole, angled five wide through the turn and dug in gamely through the final sixteenth. MO EH HENNESSY pressured the pace three wide through the backstretch, dropped back midway on the turn but came back to take third late. TRICKY STRONG raced with a pressured early pace toward the inside, contested even terms at the rail on the turn but dropped back past the eighth pole and flattened in the lane. FROSTY THE BULL raced with the pace two deep while between horses but dropped back midway on the turn and weakened in the lane. MONEY MAC gave chase outside and raced in the five path of the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Tricky Strong
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,even terms rail turn,flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Eh Hennessy
ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John and Longball Stables LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,dropped back mid turn,along 3rd late

ENTRY.NAME: Bliss This
ENTRY.OWNER: Bayne Jr William B and Super C Racing Inc

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT PASS took a quick lead and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and was steadily handled to hold well. HOLY HIP came away a bit awkwardly but picked up the chase leaving the chute, raced close off the rail on the turn but relented in the duel through the stretch. FIDDLERSHOTPLEASUR chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn at the rail, was steadily handled leaving the turn and just lasted for third. FESSIN UP gave chase, raced in the three path of the turn and just missed third in an even finish. CHANTILLY MOON (PER) chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. HEARD was not a factor. MOON WALKIN chased outside, rounded the turn about the five path and showed little in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Pass
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace,pressured 5/16,rail turn,held well driving

ENTRY.NAME: Holy Hip
ENTRY.OWNER: C M Racing Stables LLC and Lewis Jalen
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,chased,close off rail turn,relented lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 24 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 24 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,50 0 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEACHINTHERELEASE pressured the pace inside and took the nod leaving the five sixteenths pole, dueled clear past the quarter and was steadily handled in the stretch. JAZZ WITH DENIS pressured the pace three wide through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the three path, dug in under steady stretch handling and just lasted for second. KAYLEE'S SPITFIRE was shuffled back at the start, gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn about the six path, finished well and just missed second. DE'S CASTLE gave chase, raced in the three path of the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. RIVER ROYALE R V F gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail then flattened in the stretch. CATS DIAMOND BOY contested the pace off the rail, gave up the nod leaving the five sixteenths pole, dropped back past the quarter and weakened in the stretch. IN HIGH GEAR was not a factor and rounded the turn about the four path.

ENTRY.NAME: Teachintherelease
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace inside,nod past 5/16,steady handling lane

ENTRY.NAME: Kaylee's Spitfire
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back start,chased,6p turn,finished well,just missed 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 15800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 24, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since December 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $ 6,250 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANTIPOISON raced with the pace inside, dueled Prota leaving the three eighths pole, drew clear toward the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn at the rail and was steadily handled in the stretch. MR. MOX bore out into the first turn and raced in the four path through the turn, started a bid toward the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. JAMMIN STILL saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and showed little in the stretch. ROYAL CRUSADER saved ground well off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn but showed little more. LADDIE LIAM saved ground racing well back on the opening turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, angled to the six path on the far turn, left the turn outside and passed some rivals. RRACE DAY WARRIOR was forced outward entering the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but showed little response. RAISE A SPEIGHTS settled inside on the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but weakened approaching the far turn. PROTA raced with the early pace two deep, dueled Antipoison from the three eighths pole but dropped back toward the five sixteenths and weakened off the rail on the far turn. The Stewards reviewed then dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Mr. Mox for interference into the first turn, lodged by the rider of Rrace Day Warrior.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Mox
ENTRY.COMMENT: bore out into 1st turn,4p turn,bid 3/8,off rail turn,flatten late

ENTRY.NAME: Laddie Liam
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground well back,chased 3/8,6p far turn,passed rivals

ENTRY.NAME: Rrace Day Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: Boggs M Joanna and Shade Tree Farm LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Prota
ENTRY.OWNER: A and B Racing Stable LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 24 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 24 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGGIE'S GIRL pressured the pace from the three eighths pole and took the lead two deep toward the quarter, drew clear midway on the turn, was kept sharp through the upper stretch but finished of her own initiative the final sixteenth. LA MADDALENA chased through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn, dueled for second later yards and finished well. CRAFTY WINDSOR CAT took over while angling to the inside and set a pressured pace, was met a the rail toward the quarter pole, dropped back midway on the turn and flattened later yards. SILVER RULES became a bit edgy in the gate then gave chase, raced in the three path on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. SPARKLEINYOUREYE chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn and flattened in the lane. OUR GREAT NOTION chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail and weakened in the stretch. PATTI BLUE EYES broke a step slow, gave chase and rounded the turn about the six path. ESSENTIAL MAGIC gave chase, entered the turn about the five path then faded through the turn.

ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John Cash is King LLC and LC Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Essential Magic
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: Maggie's Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,up 2d near 1/4,clear turn,own initiative late

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met rail near 1/4,flattened later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 92. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 21800. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 24, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 24 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 24 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVER COMPROMISE eased off the rail and stalked from the three quarter pole, challenged toward the seven sixteenths, took the nod past the quarter and contested the far turn at even terms two deep, dueled clear mid-stretch and widened through later yards. AUBURN MILL closed to the front while tapering to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was met past the quarter and contested even terms at the rail on the far turn and remained a factor through the upper stretch before flattening stride. MARTIN MAN settled close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and flattened in the lane. GOLDEN APPEAL rated close inside on the opening turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened stride. RIGHTEOUS MAN raced off the pace in the three path on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and showed little in the lane. MASTER THIS raced off the pace in the four path the first turn, left the turn outside and gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, but showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: Chesapeake Charlie
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,4p far turn,little in lane

ENTRY.NAME: Martin Man
ENTRY.OWNER: A and B Racing Stable LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PYEONG CHANG raced well back off the rail on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, improved in the four path of the far turn and dug in for the lead later yards. LOVERBOY LOU rounded the first turn about the four path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, took the lead in the three path midway on the far turn and dug in at the head of the lane, but was caught in later yards. SUBJECT TO CHANGE rated close inside the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for third. BOMBOLONI raced with the pace, dueled with the nod past the seven sixteenths pole, drew clear toward the five sixteenths, was met at the rail midway on the far turn, continued close through the upper stretch but flattened later yards. CARTE BLANCHE settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and showed little in the lane. SARGENT KOBE was jostled at the break, saved ground on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. HE'S ORIENTATE came out and made contact with Sargent Kobe leaving the gate then closed to even terms approaching the three quarter pole, gave chase past the seven sixteenths but dropped back at the five sixteenths and faded at the rail on the far turn. ANVIL ducked in and made contact with Sargent Kobe leaving the gate, raced in the three path on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole but faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: well back,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,4p far turn,up later yards

ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased 7/16,rail far turn,little in lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 24, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered F or $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOUGH TO TAME raced in the three path the first turn, started a bid leaving the half mile pole and drew to even terms five wide approaching the head of the lane, dug in determinedly with the lead past the eighth pole and edged clear later yards. CHARLIE POTATOES saved ground on the first turn, bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole but raced hemmed in in the three path midway on the far turn, eased to the six path toward the head of the lane and dueled through the stretch to take second later yards. ANOTHER VICTORY rounded the opening turn in the three path, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the six path on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. LANTAU rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, was met at the rail approaching the head of the lane and remained close to mid-stretch before flattening stride. ROYAL THUNDER rounded the opening turn about the four path and stalked leaving the turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, closed to even terms four wide approaching the head of the lane and raced close through the upper stretch before flattening stride. HAPPY CHAMP rated close inside, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but lacked room at the rail midway on the far turn, dueled close in the upper stretch then flattened later yards. COWBOY AT HEART broke through prior the start then stalked off the rail, challenged leaving the three eighths pole, dueled at even terms two deep while between horses toward the top of the stretch but weakened leaving the eighth pole.
